# Frontend Next.js Rules

## Architecture
- Use Next.js 14+ with App Router
- Use React 19 with TypeScript
- Follow component composition patterns
- Implement proper state management with TanStack React Query

## UI Framework
- Use Chakra UI v3 for all UI components
- Follow Design System from `docs/03_DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`
- Use design tokens for consistent styling
- Implement responsive design patterns

## Component Structure
- Create reusable components in `src/components/`
- Use proper TypeScript interfaces for props
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use React.memo for performance optimization

## State Management
- Use TanStack React Query for server state
- Use React Context for global UI state
- Use local state for component-specific data
- Implement proper loading and error states

## Routing
- Use Next.js App Router conventions
- Implement proper page layouts
- Use dynamic routes for resource IDs
- Implement proper navigation patterns

## Forms and Validation
- Use React Hook Form for form management
- Use Zod for client-side validation
- Implement proper form error handling
- Use controlled components

## Performance
- Implement proper code splitting
- Use dynamic imports for large components
- Optimize images with Next.js Image component
- Implement proper caching strategies

## Testing
- Write unit tests for components
- Use Playwright for E2E testing
- Test user interactions and workflows
- Mock API calls in tests

## Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Implement proper ARIA attributes
- Ensure keyboard navigation
- Test with screen readers

## SEO
- Use proper meta tags
- Implement structured data
- Use Next.js Head component
- Optimize for Core Web Vitals